{
  "texts": [
    "Jailbreaking involves bypassing or altering the model's built-in restrictions to produce responses that are normally censored or access blocked functionalities.",
    "This is done by \"tricking\" the model to be in developer or otherwise unrestricted mode (Huang et al., 2023; Wei A. et al., 2023; Deng et al., 2024; Jiang et al., 2024).",
    "• Prompt injection.",
    "Prompt injection involves a malicious third party intercepting the prompt sent by the user to the LLM.",
    "The third party modifies or fully replaces the user prompt by a different prompt."
  ]
}